    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-16T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13775: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-16T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 16, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 16—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>618. Hankow’s December 15, 5 p.m.<note n="90" xml:id="d556fn90">Not
                        printed.</note> Embassy here telegraphed this morning to an American
                    missionary in Sian, requesting him to report by telegraph concerning safety and
                    welfare of American citizens in Sian and vicinity.<note n="91" xml:id="d556fn91"
                        >This request followed the seizure of Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek by
                        mutinous military leaders at Sian.</note> Telegraph office here accepted
                    message and will endeavor to ascertain whether it is delivered. Telegraph line
                    is reported open to Sian but messages are subject to delay in delivery and
                    censorship.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Nanking, Shanghai and Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
